content:
The Insurance Agent Console is where customer service representatives (CSRs) can view a timeline of interactions with the customer, get contextual alerts, take relevant actions, and search for knowledge articles.

The console comes with preconfigured Service Excellence components and platform capabilities:

* View profile card: CSRs can get the profile view of the customer with relevant details.
* Analyze the customer experience: Know the current sentiment of the customer based on past engagements.
* Track interactions with Customers: Ensure continuity in engagements with a chronological, interactive timeline of all interactions.
* Take relevant actions: Use the Action Launcher to quickly find and run service actions, such as uploading documents or configuring own actions to launch flows and/or OmniScripts.
* View policy details: Get a consolidated view of all policies held by the customer.

Get contextual alerts on related activities like upcoming premium due dates, policy renewal, and new claims. Configure components to work with other standard navigation apps.

In Lightning App Builder, drag standard components from the Components panel to the Lightning page canvas.

Prerequisites for Setting Up the Insurance Agent Console include reviewing prerequisites and considerations to set up and use the Service Console for Insurance customers.

Get Access to Insurance Agent Console by enabling the Service Excellence for Insurance setting for your org.
title: Setting Up the Insurance Agent Console
